Book of Hours, Use of Rome

Free Library of Philadelphia, Lewis E 116. Italy, Circa 1450. This manuscript is a fifteenth-century Italian Book of Hours, Use of Rome. It is a small-scale volume of text only, with rubrication and catchwords its only decoration. The text comprises the Hours of the Virgin, the Office of the Dead, partial Hours of the Cross, and Hours of the Holy Spirit.
